Α; Alpha; ox head. Strength / Leader.
Β; Beta; house. House / Dwelling.
Γ; Gamma; throw-stick. Walk / Carry.
Δ; Delta; tent flap. Door / Threshold.
Ε; Epsilon; figure with raised arms. Behold / Breath.
Ζ; Zeta; weapon. Cut / Nourish.
Η; Eta; wall. Separate / Protect.
Θ; Theta; basket. Surround / Contain.
Ι; Iota; hand. Work / Deed.
Κ; Kappa; open palm. Open / Allow.
Λ; Lambda; shepherd's staff. Teach / Direct.
Μ; Mu; water. Chaos / Mighty.
Ν; Nu; sprout. Continue / Heir.
Ξ; Xi; prop. Support / Grasp.
Ο; Omicron; eye. See / Know.
Π; Pi; mouth. Speak / Open.
Ρ; Rho; head. Head / First.
Σ; Sigma; teeth. Press / Consume.
Τ; Tau; mark. Mark / Covenant.
Υ; Upsilon; forked branch. Connect / Choose.
Φ; Phi; circle bisected. Whole Divided.
Χ; Chi; intersecting strokes. Cross / Exchange.
Ψ; Psi; trident. Breath / Soul.
Ω; Omega; closing circle. End / Great Whole.

Letters Α through Τ inherit Phoenician pictographs directly. Letters Υ through Ω are Greek inventions; their roles derive from letterform and Greek-internal semantic function rather than Phoenician inheritance.

Details about other literary systems can be found at https://keyofenglish.com/glyphs
